
= Swedish-born ridesharing movement

URL = https://www.facebook.com/ridesharingmovement/

=Description=

Mattias Jägerskog:

"Skjutsgruppen (www.skjutsgruppen.nu) is becoming The Ridesharing Movement - and the code will be released as open source so everyone everywhere can start ridesharing movements! You can be a part of this from the beginning!

The north is coming :-) . We've been building our Swedish non-profit ridesharing movement Skjutsgruppen for almost ten years now, gathering 70 000 participants. Started as an idea in 2007 we're now an participatory driven movement where we either share equally or offer rides for free in all kinds of vehicles. Every single participant has the same equal and democratic rights over both their rides and our movement as a whole - our budget, who should be in the board, who we're partnering with, the celebration of the yearly International ‪#‎RidesharingDay‬ (now gathering over 17 countries), our development and so on. We call this "participatory culture"."
